cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it deals with the fundamental problem of hand-eye calibration in robot vision. It may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it involves identifying the transformation between a camera and an end-effector. The use of covariance propagation methods suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The problem formulation and mathematical approach may also make it relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the use of synthetic and real calibration data suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
